  <title>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">Zambia - Drought (Food Insecurity)</narrative>
  </title>
  <description type="2">
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">Livelihoods and Basic Needs, Health, WASH and PG&amp;I.</narrative>
  </description>
  <description type="1">
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">Overall Operational objective is to provide support for basic needs including food (through cash-based interventions (CBI); Health, WASH; restore and strengthen livelihoods for 9,510 household in the Southern and Western provinces for a period of 18 months.</narrative>
  </description>
  <description type="1">
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">The 2018/2019 rain season was characterized by low rainfall and prolonged dry spells which negatively affected the agriculture sector, particularly crop and livestock production.</narrative>
  </description>
  <description type="3">
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">The ZRCS proposes to support a total of 57,064 individuals (9,510 HHs)</narrative>
  </description>
